directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place apples in a greased 1-qt. baking dish. In a small bowl, combine sugar, cider, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger; pour over apples. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with nuts. , Bake, uncovered, until apples are tender, 45-60 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.
name: Baked Apple Slices
ingredients:
3 large tart apples, peeled and sliced
3/4 cup sugar
1/4 cup apple cider or juice
1 tablespoon all-purpose flour
1 tablespoon ground cinnamon
1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg
1/4 teaspoon ground ginger
1/4 cup butter
1/2 cup walnuts or raisins
Vanilla ice cream
